{"data":[{"name":"100:1","price":"क़सम है उन घोड़ों की, जो पेट से साँस की आवाज़ निकालते हुए डौड़ने वाले हैं!","arabic":"وَٱلۡعَٰدِيَٰتِ ضَبۡحٗا","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6147,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wal-ʿādiyāti ḍabḥan ","translations":["By the racers","panting","(1)"],"transliterationArr":["wal-ʿādiyāti","ḍabḥan",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1840],[2,1840,2865]]}},{"name":"100:2","price":"फिर टाप मारकर चिंगारियाँ निकालने वाले घोड़ों की क़सम!","arabic":"فَٱلۡمُورِيَٰتِ قَدۡحٗا","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6148,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fal-mūriyāti qadḥan ","translations":["And the producers of sparks","striking","(2)"],"transliterationArr":["fal-mūriyāti","qadḥan",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1810],[2,1810,2785]]}},{"name":"100:3","price":"फिर सुबह के समय हमला करने वाले (घोड़ों) की क़सम!","arabic":"فَٱلۡمُغِيرَٰتِ صُبۡحٗا","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6149,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fal-mughīrāti ṣub'ḥan ","translations":["And the chargers","(at) dawn","(3)"],"transliterationArr":["fal-mughīrāti","ṣub'ḥan",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1680],[2,1680,2715]]}},{"name":"100:4","price":"फिर उससे धूल उड़ाते हैं।","arabic":"فَأَثَرۡنَ بِهِۦ نَقۡعٗا","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6150,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fa-atharna bihi naqʿan ","translations":["Then raise","thereby","dust","(4)"],"transliterationArr":["fa-atharna","bihi","naqʿan",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1000],[2,1000,1760],[3,1760,2695]]}},{"name":"100:5","price":"फिर वे उसके साथ (दुश्मन की) सेना के बीच घुस जाते हैं।","arabic":"فَوَسَطۡنَ بِهِۦ جَمۡعًا","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6151,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"fawasaṭna bihi jamʿan ","translations":["Then penetrate (in the) center","thereby","collectively","(5)"],"transliterationArr":["fawasaṭna","bihi","jamʿan",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1060],[2,1060,1740],[3,1740,3245]]}},{"name":"100:6","price":"निःसंदेह इनसान अपने पालनहार का बड़ा कृतघ्न (नाशुक्रा) है।","arabic":"إِنَّ ٱلۡإِنسَٰنَ لِرَبِّهِۦ لَكَنُودٞ","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6152,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"inna al-insāna lirabbihi lakanūdun ","translations":["Indeed","mankind","to his Lord","(is) surely ungrateful","(6)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","al-insāna","lirabbihi","lakanūdun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1170],[2,1170,3420],[3,3420,4730],[4,4730,7605]]}},{"name":"100:7","price":"और निःसंदेह वह इसपर स्वयं गवाह है।[1]","arabic":"وَإِنَّهُۥ عَلَىٰ ذَٰلِكَ لَشَهِيدٞ","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6153,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"1. (1-7) इन आरंभिक आयतों में मानवजाति (इनसान) की कृतघ्नता का वर्णन किया गया है। जिसकी भूमिका के रूप में एक पशु की कृतज्ञता को शपथ स्वरूप उदाहरण के लिए प्रस्तुत किया गया है। जिसे इनसान पोसता है, और वह अपने स्वामी का इतना भक्त होता है कि उसे अपने ऊपर सवार करके नीचे ऊँचे मार्गों पर रात-दिन की परवाह किए बिना दौड़ता और अपनी जान जोखिम में डाल देता है। परंतु इनसान जिसे अल्लाह ने पैदा किया, समझबूझ दी और उसके जीवन यापन के सभी साधन बनाए, वह उसका उपकार नहीं मानता और जानबूझ कर उसकी अवज्ञा करता है, उसे इस पशु से सीख लेनी चाहिए।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-innahu ʿalā dhālika lashahīdun ","translations":["And indeed, he","on","that","surely (is) a witness","(7)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-innahu","ʿalā","dhālika","lashahīdun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1950],[2,1950,2630],[3,2630,3560],[4,3560,6685]]}},{"name":"100:8","price":"और निःसंदेह वह धन के मोह में बड़ा सख़्त है।[2]","arabic":"وَإِنَّهُۥ لِحُبِّ ٱلۡخَيۡرِ لَشَدِيدٌ","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6154,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"2. इस आयत में उसकी कृतघ्नता का कारण बताया गया है कि जिस इनसान को सर्वाधिक प्रेम अल्लाह से होना चाहिए, वही अत्याधिक प्रेम धन से करता है।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-innahu liḥubbi al-khayri lashadīdun ","translations":["And indeed he","in (the) love","(of) wealth","(is) surely intense","(8)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-innahu","liḥubbi","al-khayri","lashadīdun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2090],[2,2090,2930],[3,2930,3840],[4,3840,7055]]}},{"name":"100:9","price":"तो क्या वह नहीं जानता, जब क़ब्रों में जो कुछ है, निकाल बाहर किया जाएगा?","arabic":"۞ أَفَلَا يَعۡلَمُ إِذَا بُعۡثِرَ مَا فِي ٱلۡقُبُورِ","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6155,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"afalā yaʿlamu idhā buʿ'thira mā fī al-qubūri ","translations":["But does not","he know","when","will be scattered","what","(is) in","the graves","(9)"],"transliterationArr":["afalā","yaʿlamu","idhā","buʿ'thira","mā","fī","al-qubūri",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,910],[2,910,1750],[3,1750,2470],[4,2470,3400],[5,3400,3750],[6,3750,3980],[7,3980,7065]]}},{"name":"100:10","price":"और जो कुछ सीनों में है, वह प्रकट कर दिया जाएगा।[3]","arabic":"وَحُصِّلَ مَا فِي ٱلصُّدُورِ","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6156,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"3. (9-10) इन आयतों में सावधान किया गया है कि सांसारिक जीवन के पश्चात एक दूसरा जीवन भी है तथा उसमें अल्लाह के सामने अपने कर्मों का उत्तर देना है, जो प्रत्येक के कर्मों का ही नहीं, उनके सीनों के भेदों को भी प्रकाश में ला कर दिखा देगा कि किसने अपने धन तथा बल का कुप्रयोग कर कृतघ्नता की है, और किसने कृतज्ञता की है। और प्रत्येक को उसका प्रतिकार भी देगा। अतः इनसान को धन के मोह में अंधा तथा अल्लाह का कृतघ्न नहीं होना चाहिए, और उसके सत्धर्म का पालन करना चाहिए।","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"waḥuṣṣila mā fī al-ṣudūri ","translations":["And is made apparent","what","(is) in","the breasts","(10)"],"transliterationArr":["waḥuṣṣila","mā","fī","al-ṣudūri",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1120],[2,1120,1530],[3,1530,1730],[4,1730,4815]]}},{"name":"100:11","price":"निःसंदेह उनका पालनहार उस दिन उनके बारे में पूरी ख़बर रखने वाला है।[4]","arabic":"إِنَّ رَبَّهُم بِهِمۡ يَوۡمَئِذٖ لَّخَبِيرُۢ","category":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat"],"ayahNumber":6157,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"4. अर्थात वह सूचित होगा कि कौन क्या है, और किस प्रतिकार का भागी है?","lang":"hi","meta":{"transliteration":"inna rabbahum bihim yawma-idhin lakhabīrun ","translations":["Indeed","their Lord","about them","that Day","(is) surely All-Aware","(11)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","rabbahum","bihim","yawma-idhin","lakhabīrun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1310],[2,1310,3300],[3,3300,3900],[4,3900,5100],[5,5100,8715]]}}],"chapter":["100 (Al-Aadiyat)","Al-Aadiyat","Surah Al-Aadiyat","Chapter Al-Aadiyat","Aadiyat","Surah Aadiyat","Chapter Aadiyat","Al Aadiyat","Surah Al Aadiyat","Chapter Al Aadiyat","Surah 100","Chapter 100","The Chargers","العاديات"],"version":{"key":"hindi_omari","direction":"ltr","language_iso_code":"hi","version":"1.1.4","last_update":1675069101,"title":"Hindi Translation","description":"Translation of the Quran meanings into Indian by Azizul-Haqq Al-Umary."}}